                  <p><tt style="font-size: 21px;">itools</tt> is a
                  Python meta-package, see the right column for a
                  summary of what <tt>itools</tt> provides.</p>

                  <h4>Download</h4>

                  <p>- <a href=
                  "../download/itools/itools-0.7.4.tar.gz">itools
                  0.7.4</a><br />
                  - <a href=
                  "../download/itools/itools-0.6.4.tar.gz">itools
                  0.6.4</a><br />
                  - <a href=
                  "../download/itools/itools-0.5.1.tar.gz">itools
                  0.5.1</a><br />
                  - <a href=
                  "http://deb.oursours.net/unstable/">Debian
                  Packages</a><br /></p>

                  <h4>Documentation and Support</h4>- <a href=
                  "../download/itools/itools-20050223.pdf">The
                  official itools documentation</a> (PDF).<br />
                  - The <a href=
                  "http://in-girum.net/mailman/listinfo/ikaaro">Mailing
                  list</a><br />

                  <h4>Source archives</h4>- <a href=
                  "http://in-girum.net/cgi-bin/archzoom.cgi/jdavid@itaapy.com--public/itools?expand">
                  The trunk</a><br />
                  - <a href=
                  "http://arch.oursours.net/zoom/herve@oursours.net--public/itools?expand">
                  Herv√©'s branch</a>
                </td>

                <td width="50%" valign="top">
                  <dl>
                    <dt><tt><b>itools.uri</b></tt></dt>

                    <dd>an API to manage URIs, to identify and
                    locate resources.</dd>

                    <dt><tt><b>itools.resources</b></tt></dt>

                    <dd>an abstraction layer over resources that
                    let to manage them with a consistent API,
                    independently of where they are stored.</dd>

                    <dt><tt><b>itools.handlers</b></tt></dt>

                    <dd>resource handlers infrastructure (resource
                    handlers are non persistent classes that add
                    specific semantics to resources). This package
                    also includes several handlers out of the
                    box.</dd>

                    <dt><tt><b>itools.xml</b></tt></dt>

                    <dd>XML infrastructure, includes resource
                    handlers for XML, XHTML and HTML documents.
                    Plus the Simple Template Language.</dd>

                    <dt><tt><b>itools.i18n</b></tt></dt>

                    <dd>tools for language negotiation and text
                    segmentation.</dd>

                    <dt><tt><b>itools.workflow</b></tt></dt>

                    <dd>represent workflows as automatons, objects
                    can move from one state to another through
                    transitions, classes can add specific semantics
                    to states and transitions.</dd>

                    <dt><tt><b>itools.catalog</b></tt></dt>

                    <dd>An Index &amp; Search engine.</dd>
                  </dl>
                </td>
